reviews.text: Very clean station and staff very helpful especially Dave who help us get a taxi free of charge after our train got delayed very grateful

Don't move to Barnham if you work in london as you may be late for work or may not get back home as the train services are poor.  Barnham is getting to busy now and over building is killing this lovely place.

We had to change at barnham station today at 11th july on platform 2. When we got off the train we had small crawling insects all over us. I believe there is something falling off from the ceilings at this station . There was no signs of anything. I think the staff at the station need to check as this is very disgusting. We were on our way for graduation and this ruined our day

Absolutely normal train station, the bin was open but cafe closed. But to be fair it was a Sunday night. 

All looked clean enough, although could do with a lick of paint. 

Waiting room was open which was good
